<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1910-12-24T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1910-12-24T00:00:00-05:00" n="123" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d123">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 701.2511/56.</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the <gloss type="to">Chilean Chargé</gloss>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1910-12-24"><hi rend="italic">December 24,
                                    1910</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">My Dear Mr. Chargé d’affaires</hi>: I beg to notify
                            you that the battleship <hi rend="italic">Delaware</hi> has been
                            detailed as the vessel of the United States to convey to Chile the
                            remains of the late Minister Anibal Cruz.</p>
                        <p>I am, etc.,</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">P. C. Knox.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>